SIMPLE: popular
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Popular
<hw>Pop"u*lar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>popularis</ets>, fr. <ets>populus</ets> people: cf. F.
<ets>populaire</ets>. See <er>People</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or
pertaining to the common people, or to the whole body of the people, as
distinguished from a select portion; <as>as, the <ex>popular</ex> voice;
<ex>popular</ex> elections.</as></def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Popular</xex>
states.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Bacon.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧So the <xex>popular</xex> vote
inclines.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Milton.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The men commonly held in <qex>popular</qex> estimation are
greatest at a distance.</q> <rj><qau>J. H. Newman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Suitable to common people; easy to be comprehended;
not abstruse; familiar; plain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Homilies are plain <qex>popular</qex> instructions.</q>
<rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Adapted to the means of the common people; possessed
or obtainable by the many; hence, cheap; common; ordinary; inferior;
<as>as, <ex>popular</ex> prices; <ex>popular</ex>
amusements.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The smallest figs, called <qex>popular</qex> figs, . . . are, of
all others, the basest and of least account.</q>
<rj><qau>Holland.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Beloved or approved by the people; pleasing to
people in general, or to many people; <as>as, a <ex>popular</ex>
preacher; a <ex>popular</ex> law; a <ex>popular</ex>
administration.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Devoted to the common people; studious of the favor
of the populace.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Such <qex>popular</qex> humanity is treason.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <def>Prevailing among the people; epidemic; <as>as, a
<ex>popular</ex> disease</as>.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Popular action</b></col> <fld>(Law)</fld>, <cd> an action
in which any person may sue for penalty imposed by statute.</cd>
<rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Populares</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
